                  <additions>
                    <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#ir #iv #iir"/> Ps 118:75–108, possibly from another manuscript</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#166v"/> Record that there was a military expedition to Eritrea on <date calendar="ethiopian" when="1968" when-custom="1976" evidence="internal">፷፰ግንቦት፡ ፲፮ቅን</date>Gənbot 16, [19]68 EC (May 24, 1976) that returned on <date calendar="ethiopian" when="1968" when-custom="1976" evidence="internal">ስኔ፡ ፲ቀን፡</date>Səne 10, [19]68 (June 17, 1976), copied thrice</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#167v"/> Calendar of the Apostles and Evangelists</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <desc>
                          Overlooked words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#1v #29v #47r #55r #76r #77r #78v"/>, etc.);
                          and overlooked lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#9v #14v #60v #105r #132v"/>, etc.);
                          and interlinearly with a symbol (┴) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#102v"/>, line 18),
                          and in the upper margin where the symbol (┴) is used (<locus target="#136v"/>, line 4),
                          and in another case where the symbol (+) is used (<locus target="#10v"/>, line 6, <locus target="#64v"/>, line 5, <locus target="#77v"/>, line 21, <locus target="#78v"/>,
                          line 6 and <locus target="#164v"/>, line 14)</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <desc>
                          The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an
                          appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe completes the line of text above or below the end of the line (throughout).
                          This scribe will also reduce the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (throughout)
                        </desc>
                        </item>

                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>The general condition of the vellum is quite clean and relatively unworn</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#26"/> has been cut off about 85 mm from the gutter. A replacement piece of parchment has been sewn onto the fore edge (with a narrow leather strip) to restore the folio</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#167"/> blank</desc>
                        </item>
                    </list>
